article.headline: Charlotte 76, Davidson 65
article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- Curtis Withers had 14 points and 11 rebounds to lead Charlotte to a 76-65 victory over Davidson on Thursday. Kevin Johnson added 13 points for the 49ers (5-2), who avenged a loss to the Wildcats last year and regained possession of the Hornets Nest Trophy, given annually to the winner of the game matching the Charlotte-area rivals. Brendan Winters scored 21 points and Logan Kosmalski added 16 for the Davidson (2-5). The Wildcats committed 22 turnovers, losing to Charlotte for the seventh time in the past eight meetings. The 49ers lead the series 23-9. Charlotte, which trailed most of the first half, used full-court pressure defense to force four consecutive Davidson turnovers and take a 48-44 lead on Withers' putback with 15:20 left. Johnson's layup off a no-look pass from Demon Brown capped a 19-2 run that put Charlotte ahead 61-46 with 8:12 remaining. The Wildcats had just one field goal in more that eight minutes during the spurt as it continued its tough non-conference schedule. Davidson has also lost to Texas Tech, North Carolina and Georgetown and will visit Duke on Dec. 29. Davidson went on a 9-0 run to cut the lead to 64-58 with 5:03 left before Charlotte reeled off four unanswered points to clinch its second straight victory. The 49ers shot 3-of-22 from 3-point range but outrebounded Davidson 41-31 and took 20 more free throws. The Wildcats, who have lost two straight, got nine points from Winters in a 13-4 run to take a 20-16 lead with 7:12 left in the first half.
